>Description:
The font menu in an editor created by "append-editor-font-menu gives a font background of black when you select gray for background colour.

I'm using racket 5.3.6 on windows 7
>How-To-Repeat:
#lang racket/gui

(define f (new frame% [label "Simple Edit"]
                      [width 200]
                      [height 200]))
(define c (new editor-canvas% [parent f]))
(define t (new text%))
(send c set-editor t)
(define mb (new menu-bar% [parent f]))
(define m-edit (new menu% [label "Edit"] [parent mb]))
(define m-font (new menu% [label "Font"] [parent mb]))
(append-editor-operation-menu-items m-edit #f)
(append-editor-font-menu-items m-font)
(send f show #t)

selecting menu item font->background->gray gives font background of black not gray.
>Fix:
